reviews.text: A popular Chinese restaurant serving classic Cantonese dishes. Signature dishes include BBQ pork, roasted pork belly, crispy chicken and sweet and Sour pork. Located in a touristy area, the restaurant is popular with locals and tourists alike. Dim sum is available during lunch time.
Nice place to chat with fds with quality dim sum
Comfortable atmosphere.  Din sum and dishes are tasteful.  Staff is nice.
This is the restaurant of choice for our Hong Kong Family. We are always here for dinner several times during our visit to HK. The staff are friendly and efficient. The desserts are the best😋

I had Dim Sum at Loong Yuen on a Saturday morning. at around 11AM. The restaurant was practically empty at that time except for one big table with almost 10 people. And we were being placed next to them. We asked for another table as we already knew the other table would be loud given the number of people there. Our request was denied and we were surrounded by 3 waitresses plus the receptionist immediately telling us why the table given to us was our best option.

After sitting for about 5 minutes, we found that was a mistake, We found ourselves competing with the next table by speaking louder and louder. We demanded and successfully changed the table. However, we were given black faces and were ignored for the rest of the time. We were given cold shoulder even when we thank the receptionist for changing the table.

Given it is part of the Holiday Inn and part of a 5 stars hotel. We are very disappointed with the services and treatment received. For the record, the restaurant is still very much empty when we left.

reviews.text: 啲價錢都可以，出品尚算可以，座位仍算寛敞，在這遊客區不可多得的食肆。
地方裝修，美倫美奐，食物味道很滋味！是一間高級好食肆！
食物少許淡， 侍應個個都木口木面， 有些黑口黑面好似好唔滿意啲客咁， 平價酒樓員工為人客拍照時 也會表示 親民， 但有一個著黑色西裝的員工， 不知是不是部長的 員工， 腳木口木面， 顯得 很不願意的， 也許少許笑容 都是這個行業的專業表現吧!
